<BaseLayout title="Code of Conduct | North Calder Colts" description="Code of conduct for players, coaches and parents at North Calder Colts.">
  <section class="section reveal">
    <h1>Code of Conduct</h1>
    <p class="lead">These standards help us protect a positive, safe and respectful football environment.</p>

    <div class="grid two" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Players</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Show respect to teammates, coaches, officials and opponents.</li>
          <li>Listen, try your best and support your team positively.</li>
          <li>Represent the club with good behaviour at all times.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h2>Coaches & Staff</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Prioritize player welfare, safety and development.</li>
          <li>Create inclusive, age-appropriate and encouraging sessions.</li>
          <li>Communicate clearly and professionally with families.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h2>Parents & Guardians</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Encourage positively from the sidelines.</li>
          <li>Respect coaches, officials and opposition teams.</li>
          <li>Support punctual attendance and the clubâ€™s safeguarding standards.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h2>Club Standards</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Zero tolerance for abusive language or discrimination.</li>
          <li>Safeguarding concerns must be reported immediately.</li>
          <li>Breaches may lead to review and club action.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
